                            &#10149; To the biographical case study
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mt-4">Evacuation transports to Theresienstadt</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <p>
                    At the beginning of April 1945, the Bergen-Belsen concentration camp was largely evacuated by the SS due 
                    to the approaching front. Three transports by train were organized, which were supposed to take approximately 
                    6,700 prisoners to the Theresienstadt ghetto north of Prague. Lea and Zsuzsa Merényi were put on a train 
                    together with about 2,500 other prisoners on April 10, 1945. Some 14 days later, the train was liberated by 
                    Soviet soldiers near Tröbitz. During this transport alone, at least 133 prisoners perished due to inadequate 
                    care, weakness, and illness.<sup><a href="#endnote8" id="footnote8">8</a></sup>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="infobox">
                    <h4>&#128279; More on this topic</h4>
                    <p>
                        The evacuation of the Lübberstedt satellite camp. In freight cars through northern Germany
                    </p>
                    <p>
